org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.diff

Class Diff

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.diff.Diff
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operator, UnaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<TemporalGraph>, UnaryBaseGraphToValueOperator<TemporalGraph,TemporalGraph>

    public class Diff
extends Object
implements UnaryBaseGraphToBaseGraphOperator<TemporalGraph>
    Calculates the difference between two snapshots of a graph by comparing the temporal attributes of the graph elements.

    The snapshots are extracted through two given temporal predicates. The result is a temporal graph containing the union of both graph element sets. Each element gets a new property named PROPERTY_KEY whose value will be a number indicating that an element is either equal in both snapshots (0) or added (1) or removed (-1) in the second snapshot. Elements not present in either snapshots will be discarded.

    The resulting graph will not be verified, i.e. dangling edges could occur. Use the BaseGraphOperators.verify() operator to validate the graph. The graph head is preserved.
